a. Summary of CWE:
This happens when memory is not freed after it is used, causing programs to waste memory.

b. Example C code:

int *ptr = malloc(sizeof(int));

c. Remediation (fixed code):

int *ptr = malloc(sizeof(int));
free(ptr);

Explanation:
Always free memory when it is no longer needed.

d. Mitigation and detection:
Use tools like Valgrind and follow good memory management practices.
